FCP Serves

Sustainability





What We Do






Federal Capital Partners® acquires, operates and develops residential and commercial assets in the Eastern U.S. markets. In addition, we deploy capital in residential and commercial product sectors through joint venture equity, mezzanine debt, and preferred equity investments. The array of transactions we have closed highlights our breadth and flexibility. Our focus on the Eastern U.S. gives us extensive local knowledge and valuable community relationships. That local emphasis, along with disciplined underwriting and a depth of experience developing, operating, and managing assets, allows us to mitigate risks and adjust to change quickly. FCP has offices in Chevy Chase, MD, Raleigh/Durham, NC and South Florida.   Fund ManagementFCP manages over $1 billion of capital and is currently investing its third fund, a commingled, discretionary fund closed in 2015.  Our fund investments are targeted to multifamily, office, retail, industrial, manufactured housing and self-storage assets in the Eastern U.S.  FCP funds are deployed in a variety of structures, including equity, preferred equity, and mezzanine debt.







5425 Wisconsin Avenue, Suite 202  | Chevy Chase, MD 20815 (240) 395-2000


 



Federal Capital Partners | Lacy I. Rice

















